Job Description
Good influencing styles and networking abilityTeam commitmentAbility to work effectively in complex matrix organisations involving outsourced operationsStrong business analysis skills and good business awareness to drive business process improvementAbility to understand and apply new technologies/ applications to deliver effective IT solutionsDeep understanding of application development methodology, techniques and standardsProject management and delivery processesDelivery focus with quality Relevant Experience:Proven experience in business analysis and business process improvementProject management experience of at least medium sized projectsExperience of working in teams across multiple locationsExtensive knowledge of relevant processes and IT solutions in area of responsibilityExperience of business case and project contract developmentAppreciation of IT systems landscapes and impact of architecture decisions on quality and deliveryTechnical specialism in the relevant IT technologies or applications Overview of the Role of an SME Within IT Innovation the ERP/ SCM and BI CoEs are responsible for ensuring that all change introduced into our global landscapes is of high design quality, introduced in a timely, affordable and sustainable manner, at acceptable risk to ongoing operations and consistent with long- term plans for the evolution of our key landscapes There are a number of Subject Matter Expert roles across the two CoEs. Each SME will be responsible for a particular process/ application area, and within that will: An SME will be responsible for the IT design in a specific process/ application area and will also be closely involved in all build, test and go- live activity in this area.
